Thread safety
=============

Thread safety means multiple threads can access shared resource and modify data without causing inconsistencies or errors.

How to Make a List Thread-Safe?
------------------------------
1. Use synchronized wrapper to wrap a regular list:
    List<String> list = Collections.synchronizedList(new ArrayList<>());

2. Use CopyOnWriteArrayList which creates a new copy of the list on each modification:
    List<String> list = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>();


What is concurrent collection?
------------------------------
    Concurrent collections are designed to handle concurrent modifications by multiple threads without throwing exceptions.
    They use internal synchronization mechanisms to ensure thread safety while allowing concurrent access.
    example: CopyOnWriteArrayList

A race condition occurs when multiple threads access shared data and the final result depends on the timing/order of execution.


| Type                 | Thread Safety | Performance (Read) | Performance (Write) | Use Case                              |
| -------------------- | ------------- | ------------------ | ------------------- | --------------------------------      |
| Array                | No            | O(1)              | O(n)                 | Fixed size, simple data storage       |
| ArrayList            | No            | O(1)              | O(n)                 | Dynamic array, general-purpose list   |
| LinkedList           | No            | O(n)              | O(1)                 | Frequent insertions/deletions         |
| Vector               | Yes           | O(1)              | O(n)                 | Thread-safe dynamic array, legacy class |
| CopyOnWriteArrayList | Yes           | O(1)              | O(n)                 | Thread-safe list optimized for reads, infrequent writes |


| Feature           | Vector                  | CopyOnWriteArrayList  |
| ----------------- | ----------------------- | --------------------- |
| Thread Safety     | ✅ Yes                   | ✅ Yes               |
| Strategy          | 🔒 Full synchronization | 📄 Copy-on-write      |
| Read Performance  | ❌ Slow (locked)         | ✅ Fast (no lock)    |
| Write Performance | ⚖️ Moderate             | ❌ Slow (copy happens)|
| Usage             | ❌ Legacy                | ✅ Modern            |

Lock: Allowing only one thread at a time to access a resource

Problem with Locking
    Threads wait → slower performance
    Especially bad for read operations

